Hello all,

the python interface I receive the following error:

     Python 2.3.2 (#1, Dec  3 2003, 16:04:00)
     [GCC 3.2.2] on linux2
     Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more
information.

  >>> from Cantera import *
  Traceback (most recent call last):
    File "<stdin>", line 1, in ?
    File "/usr/lib/python2.3/site-packages/Cantera/__init__.py", line
7, in ?
      from gases import *
    File "/usr/lib/python2.3/site-packages/Cantera/gases.py", line 8, in ?
      import solution, constants, ck2ctml
  ImportError: No module named ck2ctml
  >>>

I have searched for the ck2ctml file on my harddrive and the only
reference is /usr/local/include/cantera/kernel/converters/ck2ctml.h. 
Any help will be greatly appreciated.

Thanks,

Joe Papac
